+# QEMU-UAE
+
+QEMU-UAE is a port of QEMU that builds as a shared library plugin for WinUAE and FS-UAE. It provides PowerPC CPU emulation for Amiga PPC accelerator cards like the CyberStorm PPC and Blizzard PPC.
+
+This version is based on **QEMU 11.0** and is a port of the original [qemu-uae](https://github.com/frode-solheim/qemu-uae) project by Frode Solheim, which was based on QEMU 2.2.
+
+## Building
+
+### Prerequisites
+
+Standard QEMU build dependencies are required. On Debian/Ubuntu:
+
+```sh
+sudo apt-get install build-essential ninja-build python3 python3-venv \
+    pkg-config libglib2.0-dev libpixman-1-dev zlib1g-dev
+```
+
+### Build Instructions
+
+```sh
+# Configure for UAE plugin build
+./configure-qemu-uae
+
+# Build
+cd build
+ninja
+```
+
+The shared library will be created at `build/qemu-uae.so`.
+
+### Build Options
+
+The `configure-qemu-uae` script configures QEMU with minimal features required for UAE:
+
+- Target: `ppc-softmmu` only
+- Builds as shared library (`qemu-uae.so`) instead of executable
+- Disables unnecessary features (SDL, GTK, VNC, KVM, etc.)
+
+Debug options can be enabled by uncommenting lines in `configure-qemu-uae`:
+
+```sh
+# EXTRA_CFLAGS="$EXTRA_CFLAGS -DDEBUG_DISAS"
+# EXTRA_CFLAGS="$EXTRA_CFLAGS -DPPC_DEBUG_DISAS"
+# EXTRA_CFLAGS="$EXTRA_CFLAGS -DPPC_DEBUG_IRQ"
+# EXTRA_CFLAGS="$EXTRA_CFLAGS -DPPC_DEBUG_TB"
+# EXTRA_CFLAGS="$EXTRA_CFLAGS -DDEBUG_MMU"
+```
+
+## Usage
+
+The `qemu-uae.so` library is loaded by WinUAE or FS-UAE to provide PPC emulation. It is typically installed via the [fs-uae-plugin-qemu-uae](https://github.com/FrodeSolheim/fs-uae-plugin-qemu-uae) project.
+
+### Installation for FS-UAE
+
+Copy `qemu-uae.so` to:
+```
+~/.local/lib/fs-uae/plugins/qemu-uae/<version>/qemu-uae.so
+```
+
+Or use the fs-uae-plugin-qemu-uae build system for proper installation.
+
+## API
+
+The library exports the following functions for UAE integration:
+
+### Initialization
+
+- `qemu_uae_init()` - Initialize QEMU subsystems
+- `qemu_uae_start()` - Start the QEMU main loop thread
+- `qemu_uae_version(int *major, int *minor, int *revision)` - Get API version
+
+### PPC CPU Control
+
+- `ppc_cpu_init(const char *model, uint32_t hid1)` - Initialize PPC CPU
+  - Supported models: `603ev`, `604e`
+- `ppc_cpu_reset()` - Reset the CPU
+- `ppc_cpu_run_continuous()` - Run the CPU main loop
+- `ppc_cpu_set_state(int state)` - Pause/resume CPU
+  - `PPC_CPU_STATE_PAUSED` = 0
+  - `PPC_CPU_STATE_RUNNING` = 1
+
+### Memory Mapping
+
+- `ppc_cpu_map_memory(PPCMemoryRegion *regions, int count)` - Map memory regions
+  - Pass `count >= 0` to replace all regions
+  - Pass `count = -1` to add/modify a single region
+
+### Interrupts
+
+- `qemu_uae_ppc_external_interrupt(bool enable)` - Trigger external interrupt
+
+### Locking
+
+- `qemu_uae_lock(int type)` - Lock/unlock for thread synchronization
+  - `QEMU_UAE_LOCK_TRYLOCK` = 0
+  - `QEMU_UAE_LOCK_TRYLOCK_CANCEL` = 1
+  - `QEMU_UAE_LOCK_ACQUIRE` = 2
+  - `QEMU_UAE_LOCK_RELEASE` = 3
+
+### Callbacks (set by UAE)
+
+The UAE emulator must set these callback function pointers:
+
+- `uae_log` - Logging function
+- `uae_ppc_io_mem_read` / `uae_ppc_io_mem_write` - I/O memory access (32-bit)
+- `uae_ppc_io_mem_read64` / `uae_ppc_io_mem_write64` - I/O memory access (64-bit)
+
+## Project Structure
+
+```
+uae/
+├── api.h              - Public API declarations
+├── attributes.h       - Compiler attributes (PPCAPI)
+├── log.h              - Logging macros
+├── ppc.h              - PPC-specific API
+├── qemu.h             - QEMU integration API
+├── qemu-uae.h         - Internal header
+├── types.h            - Type definitions
+├── qemu-uae-cpu.c     - PPC CPU integration
+├── qemu-uae-main.c    - Main initialization
+├── qemu-uae-slirp.c   - Network stubs
+└── meson.build        - Build configuration
+```
+
+## Changes from Upstream QEMU
+
+The following modifications are made to QEMU for UAE support:
+
+- `system/cpus.c` - UAE mutex wrapper functions
+- `system/memory.c` - UAE logging for unassigned memory
+- `system/runstate.c` - UAE main loop integration
+- `target/ppc/translate.c` - Skip invalid bits check (CSPPC compatibility)
+- `meson.build` - Shared library build support
+- `meson_options.txt` - `qemu_uae` build option
+
